<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>전깃불 [전ː기뿔 /전ː긷뿔]</dt><br>
<dd>light</dd><br>
<dd>전등에 켜진 불.</dd><br>
<dd>The light from an electric light bulb.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>빛 [빋]</dt><br>
<dd>1. light</dd><br>
<dd>해, 달, 전등, 불 등에서 나와 사물을 밝게 비추는 것.</dd><br>
<dd>Rays that emanate from objects such as the sun or fire or an electric lamp and illuminate other objects and their surroundings.</dd><br>
<dd>2. color; complexion</dd><br>
<dd>물체가 나타내는 색깔.</dd><br>
<dd>The color that an object is shown in.</dd><br>
<dd>3. look</dd><br>
<dd>얼굴에 나타나는 표정.</dd><br>
<dd>The look on one's face.</dd><br>
<dd>4. ambience</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 느낌이 들게 하는 분위기.</dd><br>
<dd>An atmosphere that evokes a certain feeling.</dd><br>
<dd>5. glitter; glisten</dd><br>
<dd>반짝이는 사물에서 나타나는 밝고 환한 느낌.</dd><br>
<dd>The bright and radiant light that is reflected off a glittering object.</dd><br>
<dd>6. recognition; hope; ray</dd><br>
<dd>(비유적으로) 희망이나 영광.</dd><br>
<dd>(figurative) Hope or glory.</dd><br>
<dd>7. color</dd><br>
<dd>((일부 명사 뒤에 붙어))‘빛깔’의 뜻을 나타내는 말.</dd><br>
<dd>(after certain nouns) The word that means 'color.'</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>불빛 [불삗]</dt><br>
<dd>1. firelight; glow</dd><br>
<dd>타오르는 불의 빛.</dd><br>
<dd>A light of burning fire.</dd><br>
<dd>2. light; beam</dd><br>
<dd>켜 놓은 불에서 나오는 빛.</dd><br>
<dd>A ray emitted from a light that is turned on.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>불 [불]</dt><br>
<dd>1. fire</dd><br>
<dd>물질이 빛과 열을 내며 타는 것.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of a substance burning while emitting light and heat.</dd><br>
<dd>2. fire</dd><br>
<dd>집이나 물건이 불에 타는 재앙이나 재난.</dd><br>
<dd>A calamity or disaster where houses or possessions are burnt.</dd><br>
<dd>3. light</dd><br>
<dd>빛을 내어 어둠을 밝히는 물체.</dd><br>
<dd>A substance that gives out light and drives out darkness.</dd><br>
<dd>4. fire</dd><br>
<dd>(비유적으로) 불이 타는 듯이 열렬하고 거세게 타오르는 감정.</dd><br>
<dd>(figurative) A passionate and strong feeling like a burning flame.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>등불 [등뿔]</dt><br>
<dd>1. lamp</dd><br>
<dd>어두운 데를 밝히려고 등에 켠 불.</dd><br>
<dd>Light lit in a lamp to light a dark place.</dd><br>
<dd>2. light</dd><br>
<dd>등잔에 켠 불.</dd><br>
<dd>Light lit in an oil lamp.</dd><br>
<dd>3. light; hope</dd><br>
<dd>(비유적으로) 앞날에 희망을 주는 존재.</dd><br>
<dd>(figurative) A thing that gives hope for future.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>광명 [광명]</dt><br>
<dd>1. being light and bright</dd><br>
<dd>밝고 환함.</dd><br>
<dd>A compound noun meaning being light and bright.</dd><br>
<dd>2. bright future; hope</dd><br>
<dd>(비유적으로) 밝은 미래나 희망.</dd><br>
<dd>(figurative) A bright future or hope.</dd><br>
<dd>3. light</dd><br>
<dd>불교에서, 부처나 보살의 몸에서 나는 빛.</dd><br>
<dd>In Buddhism, a light from Buddha or Bodhisattva's body.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>광 [광]</dt><br>
<dd>1. shine; light</dd><br>
<dd>해, 달, 전등, 불 등에서 나와 사물을 밝게 비추는 것.</dd><br>
<dd>Something emitted by the sun, the moon, a lamp, a fire, etc., which illuminates things.</dd><br>
<dd>2. gloss; shine</dd><br>
<dd>깨끗하고 매끄러운 물체의 표면에 빛이 반사되어 보이는 윤기.</dd><br>
<dd>Gloss seen from the reflection of light on the surface of a clear and smooth object.</dd><br>
<dd>3. gwang</dd><br>
<dd>화투에서 점수가 이십 점짜리인 카드.</dd><br>
<dd>A 20-point-card in hwatu game.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>경량급 [경냥끕]</dt><br>
<dd>lightweight; light</dd><br>
<dd>선수의 몸무게에 따라 등급을 매겨서 하는 경기에서, 몸무게가 가벼운 편에 드는 등급.</dd><br>
<dd>The class for a light-weighted player in a sports match that divides players by weight.</dd><br>
